        "title": "Conditional in print statement doesn&#39;t print the rest of it. Java",
        "body": "<p>So here's a simple code to adjust the right \"st\", \"nd\", \"rd\", \"th\" with the input number. <em>It's placed in a loop for a reason. Nevermind that.<\/em><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(\"How many?\");\nint num = x.nextInt();\nfor(int i=1;i&lt;=num;i++){\n    System.out.print(\"Enter the \" + i);\n    System.out.println(i==1? (\"st\"):(i==2? \"nd\":i==3? \"rd\":\"th\") + \" number!\");\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>when num is input as <code>5<\/code> here's the output:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Enter the 1st\nEnter the 2nd number!\nEnter the 3rd number!\nEnter the 4th number!\nEnter the 5th number!\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Question is where's \"number!\" with the case \"1st\"??<\/p>\n",
